Simulated Example

Source: vignettes/01-sim-example.Rmd
01-sim-example.Rmd
library(DPH)

Here is a simulated example which shows you how to use DPH:

sim_data
#> # A tibble: 1,000 x 4
#>     time status pred1 pred2
#>    <int>  <int> <dbl> <int>
#>  1     5      1  1.37     1
#>  2     5      1  2.18     0
#>  3     1      1  1.16     0
#>  4     1      1  3.60     0
#>  5     2      1  2.33     1
#>  6     3      1  1.18     1
#>  7     1      1  2.49     0
#>  8     1      1  2.74     0
#>  9     2      1  2.58     1
#> 10     3      1  1.69     1
#> # … with 990 more rows
time <- sim_data$time
status <- sim_data$status
pred <- sim_data[, -(1:2)]

Outcome summary of the simulated data:

tbl <- table(time, status)
addmargins(tbl)
#>      status

Standard DPH Model

dph(
  time = time, 
  status = status, 
  pred = pred
)
#> $beta
#>      pred1      pred2 
#>  0.6756909 -0.0148435 
#> 
#> $lambda0
#>      time1      time2      time3      time4      time5 
#> 0.07721568 0.14293477 0.18430145 0.20137149 0.20908461

#> [1] -1432.959

ADPH Model

Case 1

adph(
  time = time, 
  status = status, 
  pred = pred,
  sens = 0.8,
  spec = 0.9
)

ADPH2 Model

system.time(
  adph2_model <- adph2(
    time = time, 
    status = status, 
    pred = pred,
    n_ptb = 100
  )
)
